<paragraph id="IAS38_111" base="SL32740" principles="no"><paranum>111</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 38"/><data name="paranum" value="111"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS38_P0303">To determine whether an <xref base="SL141716" href="IAS38_8.dita#IAS38_8/IAS38_P0070">intangible asset<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0193"/></ph></xref> is impaired, an entity applies <xref id="IAS38_X0329" base="F16456316" href="../ias36/IAS36_TOC0001.dita#IAS36_TOC0001">IAS 36</xref>. That Standard explains when and how an entity reviews the <xref base="SL141709" href="IAS38_8.dita#IAS38_8/IAS38_P0063">carrying amount<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0026"/></ph></xref>  of its assets, how it determines the recoverable amount  of an asset and when it recognises  or reverses  an <xref base="SL141715" href="IAS38_8.dita#IAS38_8/IAS38_P0069">impairment loss.<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0176"/></ph></xref></p></body></paragraph>